servers.name: database-tools
servers.aiSummary: The database-tools server is designed for database management, providing essential functionalities to interact with database tables and execute SQL queries. It integrates with database services to facilitate operations such as retrieving table structure, executing custom queries, and testing database connectivity, making it a vital tool for database administrators and developers.
aiUseCases: A database administrator uses the get_tables tool to list all tables in a database before performing a migration to ensure all relevant data structures are accounted for.
A developer utilizes the execute_query tool to run a complex SQL query that aggregates user data for reporting purposes, allowing for dynamic data analysis.

A system integrator employs the test_connection tool to verify database connectivity during the setup of a new application, ensuring that all configurations are correctly established before deployment.

toolDescriptions.name: get_table_columns
toolDescriptions.description: 获取数据库表的列信息，包括列名、类型、是否可空、注释等详细信息

toolDescriptions.name: get_tables
toolDescriptions.description: 获取数据库中所有表的信息，包括表名、注释、类型、引擎等

toolDescriptions.name: test_connection
toolDescriptions.description: 测试数据库连接是否正常

servers.name: rule-generate-tools
servers.aiSummary: The rule-generate-tools server specializes in generating data quality assessment rule sets based on database schema, evaluation metrics, and database configurations. This server integrates with data management and quality assurance processes to enhance the reliability of data through automated rule generation.
aiUseCases: A data analyst uses this server to automatically generate quality assessment rules for a new database schema, ensuring that the data adheres to predefined quality criteria before it is utilized for reporting.

A database administrator leverages the server to create tailored data quality rules based on specific evaluation metrics, allowing for improved monitoring of data integrity across multiple applications.
A data quality manager employs this tool to streamline the process of rule generation for various database configurations, facilitating quicker compliance with data governance policies.

toolDescriptions.name: generate_rules
toolDescriptions.description: 根据表结构、评估指标和数据库配置生成数据质量评估规则集

servers.name: rule-execute-tools
servers.aiSummary: The rule-execute-tools server is designed to facilitate the execution of data quality assessment rules by running SQL queries on specified databases. This server integrates with data management systems to ensure data integrity and quality, providing the capability to evaluate datasets against established criteria and return insightful assessment results.
aiUseCases: A data analyst can use this server to execute a set of predefined SQL queries that assess the quality of customer data in a CRM system, identifying any inconsistencies or inaccuracies.
A database administrator may utilize the server to run data quality rules on a new dataset before it is migrated to a production database, ensuring that only high-quality data is transferred.
A compliance officer can leverage the server to regularly evaluate the data quality of financial records against regulatory standards, generating reports that highlight any areas of concern.

toolDescriptions.name: execute_rules
toolDescriptions.description: 执行数据质量评估规则集，对指定数据库运行SQL查询并返回评估结果

servers.name: invali-data-get-tools
servers.aiSummary: The invali-data-get-tools server is designed to identify and retrieve invalid data records based on specified data quality assessment rules. It integrates with data quality management systems to enhance data integrity and reliability by providing tools to manage and rectify invalid data issues. The key capability of the available tool, 'get_invalid_data', allows users to programmatically access and analyze records deemed invalid, thereby facilitating data cleansing processes.
aiUseCases: A data analyst uses the get_invalid_data tool to extract records flagged as invalid during a quarterly data quality review, enabling targeted data cleansing efforts.

A software developer integrates the invali-data-get-tools server into a data processing pipeline to automatically identify and log invalid data entries, ensuring that only valid data is used for reporting.
A compliance officer employs the get_invalid_data function to generate a report of invalid data records for audit purposes, ensuring adherence to data governance policies.

toolDescriptions.name: get_invalid_data
toolDescriptions.description: 根据数据质量评估规则获取无效数据记录

servers.name: report-generate-tools
servers.aiSummary: The report-generate-tools server specializes in generating data quality assessment reports based on table structures, evaluation metrics, and assessment results. It integrates with data management services to enhance data governance and quality assurance processes, providing users with a robust tool to analyze and present data quality insights.
aiUseCases: A data analyst uses the server to generate a comprehensive data quality report after migrating a large dataset to ensure that all data meets specified quality standards.

A compliance officer utilizes the server to create a data quality assessment report as part of an audit process, verifying that the organization's data handling practices are in line with regulatory requirements.
A business intelligence team leverages the server to produce periodic reports on data quality metrics which help in identifying areas for improvement in their data collection processes.

toolDescriptions.name: generate_report
toolDescriptions.description: 根据表结构、评估指标和评估结果生成数据质量评估报告
